OpenBGPD Mirrors

OpenBGPD 6.6p0 portable: released November 1st, 2019

This is a port of OpenBGPD to other operating systems. It is based on portability code from the OpenNTPD, OpenSSH, and LibreSSL portable projects.

Platform Requirements

At the time of writing OpenBGPD portable is known to build and work on:

  • OpenBSD
  • Linux (Debian 9, Ubuntu 14.04)
  • FreeBSD (12.x)

OpenBGPD may work on other operating systems, newer and older, but the above ones are tested regularly by the developer. Reports (success or otherwise) are welcome. You may report bugs or submit pull requests at the GitHub project.

Signing

OpenBGPD portable releases are signed with a signify(1) public key: RWTGJEPobKfXIP1+foh6O3ZGQIDIxwB0Hp4rH6fMYGdYPQMFH2IEqxcY

They are co-signed with GPG using this public key.

Release signatures can be verified using the signify program from within the OpenBSD operating system itself, using the portable version of signify, which is available with recent Debian, Ubuntu and Arch Linux releases, or by using GPG.
